In [64]:
# Lot of categories are present for Cruise_line one hot encoding will drastically increase the dimension
# Hence mean for each specific Cruise_line is calculated and replaced in the data
# This will capture the required information that variable brings
df_Cruise_line = df[['Cruise_line','crew']]
df_Cruise_line = df_Cruise_line.groupby(['Cruise_line']).mean()
df_Cruise_line = df_Cruise_line.rename(columns = {'crew' : 'Cruise_line_mean'})
In [65]:
df = df.merge(df_Cruise_line, how='left', on = 'Cruise_line')
df.drop('Cruise_line', axis = 1, inplace = True)
df.drop('Ship_name', axis = 1, inplace = True)

# Hyper Parameter Tuning

from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV
# Number of features to consider at every split
max_features = ['auto', 'sqrt']
# Maximum number of levels in tree
max_depth = [int(x) for x in np.linspace(5, 20, num = 4)]
# Minimum number of samples required to split a node
min_samples_split = [2, 5, 10]
# Minimum number of samples required at each leaf node
min_samples_leaf = [1, 2, 5]
